1. CSS can be used to style HTML tables, making them visually appealing and improving readability.
-Using CSS, you can customize aspects like borders, spacing, background colors, text alignment, and hover effects.
2. CSS provides various properties to style fonts, allowing control over font family, size, weight, style, and line height.
For example, the font-family property sets the font type, and font-size adjusts the size.
3. CSS comments are used to add notes within your CSS code, which can help explain sections or make the code more readable. 
-Comments are added by wrapping text inside /* and */.